caption: Beautiful restaurant and good service. Shrimp tacos were well plated and were good.

The appetizers  took very long to come....as a matter of fact, everything came together. They missed the whole point of "starters". The food was okay; nothing to rave about. They also gave my teenage daughter a rum and Coke, instead of the Coke she ordered.
Loved everything I had on the menu. I’ll definitely be coming back for more. I recommend the mezcal cocktails, the guacamole, the quesadillas for starters.
The food is so flavorful. It made my day and I will definitely be back for more!
Food was good and the service was great.

New management has certainly picked up the baton and is of to great running start!!!  The food, service, presentation checks all the right boxes.  Long time patron who will continue to make Las Santas a regular culinary staple.

Met a couple friends here recently and it was a good time. Staff was very personable, the margaritas were amazing and they had happy hour! We shared the steak nachos and a few other appetizers which were all great. They have personal pods for cold weather so give them a try.
Great Guac, Great Sangria.

Las Santas is Mexican done well. The location is GREAT for outdoor dining during COVID. The menu is great for kids to share. My family ordered the family fajitas and it was enought for 4 adults to share and very tasty. So I would highly recommend this for large groups. The vibe is pretty energetic so might not be good spot for a quiet date, but still good for dinner for 2.
Food n drinks are good
Excelent Mexican Food
Service was good!

They have put up lights and plants to make the outside dinning space look really nice amd they habe a few plastic bubbles in dine in. Good atmosphere! Our waiter was also so nice and helpful. Yummy fish and pork tacos and passionfruit margaritas. Only complaint is that their plain margaritas are waaay to sweet. Go with the passionfruit margaritas - much better!!
My second time there food is good music is nice and entertaining

This place is great. The food is the best and the service was wonderful. If you eat a planet-based or vegan diet they have wonderful options for you that are filling. I had to veggie fajitas with no cheese. The veggies was grilled to wonderfulness. They have a open kitchen and are doing in door dining. Now the drinks was great and tasty.
The restaurant is beautiful but the food is okay. Their margaritas are very small for the price. Our waiter was all over the place, he basically forgot about our table.
Great margaritas and tacos!
Food was decent. Nothing to write home to mom about but good enough to return for another Saturday brunch.
Fantastic food. Nice outdoor dining set up. Good service. The worst Margaritas I've ever had.
Margarita Mondays 🍹
Good fresh food, good cocktails and reasonable prices.
Amazing food, great drinks and fun atmosphere, keep coming back for more 😃

(Translated by Google) We called by phone to ask if they had space and shade, they told us that they did and that they had a lot of shade, the surprise was very pleasant. The service was first class, the drinks, the coffee, but ... the chorizo ​​nachos that we ordered, the tostaditas were stiff, it seemed as if they had already had days before and they put them in the micro or quickly in the oil, to remove a little old, but they did not succeed. Otherwise I have no complaints.  (Original) Llamamos por teléfono para preguntar, si tenían lugar y sombra, nos dijeron que si y que tenían mucha sombra , la sorpresa fue muy grata. El servicio fue de primera , las bebidas , el café,  pero...los nachos de chorizo que pedimos , las tostaditas estaban tiesas,  parecía como si ya hubiesen tenido de días antes y las metieron al micro o rápidamente al aceite , para quitarle un poco lo viejo , pero no lo lograron . Por lo demás no tengo ninguna queja.

I visited this restaurant a few weeks ago with a friend of mine and really enjoyed the ambience. But after eating half of my food I came to notice that the quesadilla had a long strand of hair in-bedded in the cheese I was eating. Extremely disgusted as i pulled if from my mouth. I notified the waiter who apologized. Soon after I receive the bill and I was charged regular price for the whole entire meal even though I did not finish my whole entire meal after finding hair in my food. The manager did not apologize and made me pay for the meal. Never coming here again.

Good location accessible by public transportation, good food and drinks. Though seated outside because of COVID the atmosphere was filled with good vibes plus the Thursday night DJ was on point. I would return again.
Service and food was good. Nice relaxing place with some good music. Would recommend.
Delicious!!!
Amazing food, great customer service. Very clean & great music. As well as fast service. I willing definitely return.
JUANS DA MAIN MAN. Tequilas on deck!

I was very conflicted in this rating. The food was soooo good, the drinks were well made, the decor and ambiance is beautiful, but the service was TERRIBLE! We showed up and had to find our own seats, it took us almost 15 min to get a menu and that's because we actually had to call a waiter to get us a menu or we would have still been waiting. The waiters rushed us in our order and wasn't paying attention, and throughout the meal we just couldn't seem to have a waiter give us any acknowledgement. Luckily the food didn't take as long to come. If the food wasn't so damn good here and in such a great location with good seating arrangement, I would never come back. I would have given a 3.5, but instead I will give 4 stars for good food and decor.
Great food and drinks

Food and the service was excellent. The menus that they created to use on Q-scan is pure genius. I took my girlfriend there with her son for her birthday and she was very satisfied. Spanish pork was amazing. Happy hour drinks we're pretty good price. So if you want some good Spanish food in a classy place, I recommend this for you. By the way all servers speak clear English so don't be shy to order.

Just had a date here tonight. We were put on the edge of the seating area where it looks like the other table was also ignored. We were seated and brought our round of drinks and then never checked in on again. By the time we were addressed we just wanted to go. Then another person approached us asking if we needed anything. They seemed very disorganized and not to know what they were doing.  The chips and salsa were good as was the margarita I had. Maybe I’ll try again when it’s not a Monday night but honestly I’m not sure i want to.
Great costumer service and amazing food ❣

Delicious mexican food and awesome frozen margaritas. The shrimp fajitas were absolutely yummy and seasoned perfectly. The fish taco is also recommend. We also ordered the shrimp enchiladas, they were okay. Reasonable prices (just a little pricy, but worth it!). Service was really good!!! In short - go there!!
Food was ok but the service was extremely slow
Quesadilla was good. The nachos aren't the best, but the drinks are good - strong.

Only giving a 4  start review because of James. He handled everything that was going at the moment (not just with us) very well. Ive been very exciting to try this place but in my opinion if they want to succeed they need to take whoever was taking the orders (she was too rude to even bother asking for name) away from any customers.

6/2/2020: I had the pleasure ordering  take out from Las Santas. I ordered the Nachos and Quesadilla. Both dishes was tasteful and the presentation was great. I also order 3 Margarita's: Passion fruit, Blood orange and Lime. All drinks was great and definitely worth the price.  I will be returning here again. Thanks.
They cancelled our order at the last minute after we had waited nearly half an hour.

I pass this location all the time and finally decided to go in. Margarita HEAVEN. Nachos are warm and topped with all cheesey saucy deliciousness. And the quacamole is so much better than I anticipated. I'm already planning my next trip there.

# AMAZING, #BEST NEW BAR/ RESTAURANT ON THE STRIP. Highly recommend their HAPPY HOUR; After Work Mixers  $3/Taccos; $7/Margaritas You can't  go wrong. Coupled w/ fast & friendly Service is th BEST. Can't wait to go back and try out their WKND Brunch; more 2 follow 👌⚘🤩🌻😋

Lovely and quiet restaurant. Me and a friend came here before getting our rush tix at BAM. Both of us enjoyed guacamole and a little side dish along with it. Service was slow, however, and we weren’t able to get our waitress’s attention. Food came out efficiently and was yummy!
Really great food and drinks. Staff is friendly
Delicious food, nice vibe, great service 💯

Fun new spot to replace Lady's. HH deal is great and fun, but they are still working out kinks in their table service... sat @ table for ten min w.o anyone so much as filling water, before going to bar and getting much better service!

The place has a nice decor and ambience but the food is mediocre at best. I had their lunch special with chicken soup and steak taco. Chicken soup was good but it definitely raised my blood pressure with its saltiness. The steak at chipotle is at least 3 times better. I won't  be back.
Had brunch here this past weekend. Food, service was top notch. Located in a beautiful spacious restaurant. Will be coming again soon.
Better than expected. Great Vegetarian Options. Cauliflower Mole Enchiladas tastes great. Simple chips and salsa were a stand out rather than a throw in as so many other places do
Went here with a friend and loved the place. The chips and guac were excellent. I had a fish taco and steak taco and both were delicious. Good vibe in the restaurant and drinks were great too.
amazing mexican food - some of the best I've ever had and I've visited Mexico, Chicago, Florida, etc... The service is always good and friendly also
Great vibe, quality food and great drinks. Wonderful addition to the neighborhood.
laughably slow and confused service at 6pm on a Friday while half empty
Tacos were mindblowing. But needs flexibility to mix and match. And expensive

Came for brunch, so can't speak to dinner quality. But service was slow, and food was only so-so (example, sunnyside up eggs for chilaquiles should actually be runny, not like a hard boiled egg). Nice atmosphere but not worth the price.

My husband and I have dined at Las Santas three times including opening night and each experience has been great, especially thanks to the wonderful staff. The food is always fresh and the drinks are deliciously strong!  Las Santas is a great addition to the neighborhood and we look forward to dining here again!
Food was wonderful and our bartender Gabriel gave me and my friend amazing service. The manager James was very friendly and accommodating, I recommend coming for the experience.
Nice portions, tasty food.
Food was ok, but we had the verde Maria and it tasted really bad... still we had to pay for it. Slow service

When the chips and salsa are seasoned and balanced, you know the food will not disappoint. Menu is creative and not typical/boring compared to most Mexican restaurants in NYC. Flavors were robust, food was prepared and plated well, service was attentive, and decor is sleek and attractive.  If you want to impress a date or group that you have solid taste in the NY dining scene, look no further and take them here.
Delicious food and superb service.  Don't miss it.

(Translated by Google) We were there last night my wife and I, the food is of a high standard, you can order without looking too much at prices, more than fair for each course, ten fifteen euros per dish and what a meal! The service taken care of in every part, even as they are served, a romantic place to die for, I recommend arriving early for a drink at the bar and then moving on to lunch or dinner. You will remain enthusiastic ... I bet you what you want!  (Original) Ci siamo stati ieri sera io e mia moglie, il cibo è di alto livello, potrete ordinare senza star troppo a guardare i prezzi, più che giusti per ogni portata, dieci quindici euro a piatto e che piatti! Il servizio curato in ogni sua parte, anche per come vengono serviti, posto romantico da morire, consiglio di arrivare presto per una bevuta al bar per poi passare al pranzo o alla cena. Ne resterete Entusiasti...ci scommetto quello che volete!
Great food and excellent customer service. They always checked on is to make sure everything was great and let us stay as long as e we needed.
The food is unbelievable, and the service is great. I cannot wait to go back, especially to try their brunch!

Las Santas just opened and all I can say is that it’s the best Mexican restaurant in Brooklyn.  The ambiance, food, and waiters combine to provide a memorable experience.  If you want true authentic Mexican food this is the place to go.
Delicious food a nice ambience. Very attentive staff. Overall recommend! Great place for brunch or dinner.

Some of the freshest mexican cuisine you will get locally. Delicious food, great cocktails and amazing ambiance. Fine details are accounted for in everything! For some unique and amazing cocktails ask for Gabriel at the bar!
Cozy warm decor. Authentic Mexican food. Great empanadas.

Delicious and great service. Just opened a week or two ago, and already doing great!  All of the food was very flavorful and fresh, each dish was fun and a bit different. Cocktails were inventive and tasty. The servers were fast and friendly, and the atmosphere is fun (bar area for drinks/snacks in front and seated dinner in back).  There is plenty of seating which should keep it from feeling crowded as more people find it, and it doesn't seem like it'll become too loud.
The food and drinks were on point and the price was right.
Great Authentic Mexican food!

Perfect place to grab a drink after work with friends! Incredible cocktails and food, really great atmosphere, this is a great new regular spot. The nachos have been demolished and only barely survived the review process. They looked beautiful when they first came and and tasted even better!

Solid Happy Hour (4-7) with fun and knowledgeable bartenders. It's hard to beat a $7 HH margarita! The food is phenomenal; definitely try the fajita platter (large enough to feed two), or the cauliflower enchiladas.
Great food and atmosphere, I grew up eating these recipes in Mexico and to taste them here in NYC along with home made tortillas it’s amazing!
